   <concept id="FAR_10_001" class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">10.001</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d626e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Agencies shall—</p>
               <ol id="d626e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Ensure that
legitimate needs are identified and trade-offs evaluated to acquire
items that meet those needs;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e21">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Conduct
market research appropriate to the circumstances–</p>
                     <ol id="d626e42" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e27">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Before developing
new requirements documents for an acquisition by that agency;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e32">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions with an estimated value in excess
of the simplified acquisition threshold;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e37">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions with an estimated value less
than the simplified acquisition threshold when adequate information
is not available and the circumstances justify its cost;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e42">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph> Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions that could lead to consolidation
or bundling (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.644(e)(2)(A)</xref>) and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657q</xref>);</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e53">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(v)</ph> Before awarding a task or delivery order under an indefinite-delivery/indefinite-quantity (ID/IQ) contract (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.</i>, GWACs, MACs) for other than a commercial product or commercial service in excess of the simplified acquisition threshold (<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/3453"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 3453(c)</xref>); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e64">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vi)</ph> On an ongoing
basis, take advantage (to the maximum extent practicable) of commercially
available market research methods in order to effectively identify
the capabilities of small businesses and new entrants into Federal contracting
that are available in the marketplace for meeting the requirements
of the agency in furtherance of-</p>
                           <ol id="d626e110" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e70">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph> A contingency
operation or defense against or recovery from cyber, nuclear, biological,
chemical, or radiological attack; and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e75">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph> Disaster
relief to include debris removal, distribution of supplies, reconstruction,
and other disaster or emergency relief activities (See <xref href="26.205.dita#FAR_26_205"
                                          base="i1090608"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">26.205</xref>); and</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e83">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Use the
results of market research to–</p>
                     <ol id="d626e145" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e89">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Determine if
sources capable of satisfying the agency’s requirements exist;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e94">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Determine
if commercial products
or commercial services, or, to the extent commercial products suitable to meet
the agency’s needs are not available, nondevelopmental items are
available that-</p>
                           <ol id="d626e164" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e100">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph> Meet the agency’s requirements;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e105">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph> Could be
modified to meet the agency’s requirements; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e110">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph> Could meet
the agency’s requirements if those requirements were modified to
a reasonable extent;</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e115">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Determine
the extent to which commercial
products, or nondevelopmental items could be incorporated at the
component level;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e120">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph> Determine
the practices of firms engaged in producing, distributing, and supporting commercial products or commercial
services, such as type of contract, terms for warranties, buyer
financing, maintenance and packaging, and marking;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e125">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(v)</ph>
                              Ensure maximum practicable use of sustainable products and services (as defined in <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>) in accordance with <xref href="Subpart_23.1.dita#FAR_Subpart_23_1"
                                    base="i1094654"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  23.1</xref>;
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e133">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vi)</ph> Determine
whether consolidation is necessary and justified (see <xref href="7.107-2.dita#FAR_7_107_2"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">7.107-2</xref>)
(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657q</xref>);</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e144">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vii)</ph> Determine
whether bundling is necessary and justified (see <xref href="7.107-3.dita#FAR_7_107_3"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">7.107-3</xref>)
(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.644(e)(2)(A)</xref>);</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e155">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(viii)</ph> Determine
whether the acquisition should utilize any of the small business
programs in accordance with <xref href="Part_19.dita#FAR_Part_19"
                                    outputclass="fm:Part"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">part  19</xref>; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e163">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ix)</ph> Assess
the availability of supplies or services that meet all or part of
the applicable information and communication technology accessibility
standards at <xref href="https://www.federalregister.gov/select-citation/2021/08/11/36-CFR-1194.1"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">36 CFR 1194.1</xref> (see <xref href="Subpart_39.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_39_2"
                                    base="i1077004"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  39.2</xref>).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e174">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> When conducting
market research, agencies should not request potential sources to
submit more than the minimum information necessary.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e179">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> If an agency
contemplates consolidation or bundling, the agency—</p>
               <ol id="d626e289" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e185">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> When
performing market research, should consult with the agency small
business specialist and the local Small Business Administration
procurement center representative (PCR). If a PCR is not assigned,
see <xref href="19.402.dita#FAR_19_402"
                              base="i1101041"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.402</xref>(a); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e193">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Shall notify
any affected incumbent small business concerns of the Government's
intention to bundle the requirement and how small business concerns
may contact the appropriate Small Business Administration procurement
center representative (see <xref href="7.107-5.dita#FAR_7_107_5"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">7.107-5</xref>(a)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d653e201">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  See <xref href="10.003.dita#FAR_10_003"
                        base="i1114778"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10.003</xref> for the requirement
for a prime contractor to perform market research in contracts in
excess of $6 million, other than contracts for the acquisition of
commercial products or commercial services (section 826 of Pub.
L. 110-181).
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
